Module com.io7m.jregions.core
Package com.io7m.jregions.core.parameterized.areas

Class PAreaD<S>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.io7m.jregions.core.parameterized.areas.PAreaD<S>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - A phantom type parameter indicating the coordinate space of the area
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    PAreaDType<S>, AreaValuesDType, AreaSizeValuesDType

    public final class PAreaD<S>
extends java.lang.Object
implements PAreaDType<S>

    An area with double coordinates.

    The coordinates of the area are given in half-closed form. That is, minimumX() refers to the minimum inclusive value on the X axis, and maximumX() refers to the maximum exclusive value on the X axis. Likewise for the Y axis.
